==Current descendants==
The headship of the family is in dispute between [[Charles Napoléon]], born 1950, great-great-grandson of [[Jérôme Bonaparte]] by his second marriage; and his son [[Jean-Christophe Napoléon|Jean-Christophe]] (born 1986) who was appointed heir in the will of his grandfather [[Prince Louis Napoléon]]. The only other male member of the family is the brother of Charles, [[Jerome Xavier Bonaparte|Prince Jérôme]], (born 1957), unmarried. There are no remaining descendants in male line from any other of Napoleon's brothers. There are, however, numerous descendants of Napoleon's illegitimate, but recognized son [[Walewski]] from his union with [[Marie, Countess Walewski]]. Of these include the Wattier family and its union with the Bonaparte family. The later descendants were the Peschongs and Herrs. A descendant of Napoleon's sister Caroline Bonaparte is actor [[René Auberjonois (actor)|René Auberjonois]].

