==Trivia==
{{Trivia|date=June 2010}}
[[File:Becaksiantar.jpg|thumb|ight|Public &quot;Becak&quot; in Pematangsiantar (Indonesia)]]
In the [[Indonesia]]n city of [[Pematangsiantar]] (North [[Sumatra]]), all the local &quot;becaks&quot; (public transportation bikes with sidecar) are equipped with 350cc BSA (mostly B31, B32 or B40); some are also 500cc models. This is unique worldwide.&lt;ref&gt;[http://wikitravel.org/en/Pematangsiantar Wikitravel: Pematangsiantar]&lt;/ref&gt; As there are no spare parts available, most of them are individually modified, maintained and repaired.&lt;ref&gt;[http://www.trekearth.com/gallery/Asia/Indonesia/Sumatra/Sumatera_Utara/Pematangsiantar/photo523676.htm Photo from TrekEarth]&lt;/ref&gt;

