    &lt;td valign=&quot;top&quot;&gt;2¡&lt;/sub&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;/tr&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

Thus the determinant is σ&lt;sub&gt;''n''&lt;/sub&gt;(1), the [[Stirling polynomial]] at ''x'' = 1.
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
For even-numbered Bernoulli numbers, ''B''&lt;sub&gt;2''p''&lt;/sub&gt; is given by the ''p X p'' determinant:&lt;ref&gt;{{cite arxiv |eprint=1103.1585 |author1=Jerome Malenfant |title=Finite, closed-form expressions for the partition function and for Euler, Bernoulli, and Stirling numbers |class=math.NT |year=2011}}&lt;/ref&gt;
